1. e4 d6 {We are starting with the Philidor defence, analyzed in Chapter 1.} 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Bc4 Ke8 7. f4 {Let's hit directly the center pawn.} Bb4 8. Bd3 Nc6 9. Nf3 Bg4 {All theory up to now.} 10. fxe5 Nd7 11. Bf4 Bxf3 12. gxf3 Ncxe5 {This move is not so precise.} (12... Ndxe5 {is the way, and is analyzed in Chapter 1.}) 13. Be2 {Now I can go for long castle, that's the difference.} Rd8 14. Bd2 {I also like this idea, why to allow Black to damage my structure?} (14. O-O-O {This was also a normal move.}) 14... c6 15. O-O-O f6 16. Rhg1 {I really like my position now, also 16. f4 was good, I won the game in a nice fashion, check out the rest for yourself.} g5 17. f4 Bxc3 18. Bh5+ Ke7 19. Bxc3 gxf4 20. Bb4+ c5 21. Bd2 f3 22. Rg7+ Ke6 23. Bf4 Rhg8 24. Bg4+ $1 {This is what my opponent missed!} f5 (24... Nxg4 25. Rd6#) 25. Bxf5+ Kf6 26. Rxh7 f2 27. Bg3 (27. Rd6#) 27... Rxg3 28. hxg3 Nf8 29. Rhh1 Rxd1+ 30. Kxd1 Ng4 31. Ke2 Ke5 32. Bxg4 1-0

