1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Bc4 Bb4 7. Bxf7 {is the critical line, perfect for blitz, now Black needs to know it move by move.} (7. Bd2 $5 {is the other option we examine in Chapter 1.}) 7... Rf8 8. Bb3 Nxe4 9. Nge2 Nc6 $2 {This is not so precise.} (9... Nc5 $1 {is the only move for Black to get a more or less defendable endgame.}) 10. Be3 {Logical move. Protect and want to make long castle.} Nxc3 11. Nxc3 Nd4 $6 {Another strange move, this just doesn't work.} 12. O-O-O Bd6 13. Ne4 {I allowed ... Nxb3 after which Black was able to stay in the game.} (13. Bxd4 $18 {was correct, followed by Ne4, where Black will for sure lose the pawn on d4 and his king is still in the danger zone.}) 13... Nxb3+ 14. axb3 Ke7 15. Bg5+ Ke6 16. Rd3 h6 17. Be3 Be7 18. Bc5 Rf4 19. Bxe7 Kxe7 20. Re3 Bf5 21. Rhe1 Bxe4 22. Rxe4 Rxe4 23. Rxe4 Kd6 24. Rg4 g5 25. h4 Rf8 26. f3 Rf4 27. Rxf4 exf4 28. hxg5 hxg5 29. Kd2 Kd5 30. Kd3 c5 31. Kc3 b5 32. Kd3 c4+ 33. bxc4+ bxc4+ 34. Kc3 Kc5 35. Kd2 a5 36. c3 a4 37. Kc2 Kb5 38. Kb1 Kc5 39. Ka2 Kb5 40. Ka3 Ka5 41. Ka2 Kb5 42. Ka3 Ka5 43. Ka2 Kb5 1/2-1/2

